# Security Policy

## Reporting a vulnerability

Open a private vulnerability report at <https://github.com/<OWNER>/<REPO>/security/advisories/new>. Do not file a public issue.

**SLA**

- Acknowledge: 72 hours
- Triage: 7 days
- Fix critical: 30 days
- Fix high: 90 days

## Source-side audit

This repository runs [Pruner](https://github.com/ob-aion/pruner) on every pull request and tag. The signed report bundle lives on the matching GitHub release. Verify with:

```bash
gh release download <tag> --repo <OWNER>/<REPO> --pattern 'pruner-report.zip'
gh attestation verify pruner-report.zip --owner <OWNER>
```

The report covers:

- Detection via `cisco-ai-skill-scanner` (Apache-2.0, fully local).
- Coroboros policy pack — frontmatter conformance, Unicode-Tag arsenal, supply-chain hygiene.
- Secrets via `gitleaks`.
- Workflow safety via `actionlint`.
- SLSA build provenance via `actions/attest-build-provenance`.
- CycloneDX SBOM signed via `actions/attest-sbom`.

Coverage matrix: <https://github.com/ob-aion/pruner/blob/main/docs/coverage-matrix.md>.

## Out of scope

Pruner audits the published artefacts statically. Runtime monitoring, sandboxed execution, and consumer-machine behavior are out of scope.

